# Environment Variables

## Database

```env
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://user:password@cluster.mongodb.net/portfolio?retryWrites=true&w=majority
```

Generate at [MongoDB Atlas](https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas). Required for contact form storage.

## Email (Nodemailer + Gmail)

```env
EMAIL_FROM=your-email@gmail.com
GMAIL_USER=your-email@gmail.com
GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD=xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx
```

To generate `GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD`:
1. Enable 2-Factor Authentication on your Google Account
2. Go to [myaccount.google.com/apppasswords](https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords)
3. Select "Mail" and "Windows Computer" (or your device)
4. Copy the 16-character password (remove spaces)

Optional—if not set, contact form will still save to database but won't send emails.

## Development Environment

```env
NODE_ENV=development
```

## Production Environment

```env
NODE_ENV=production
MONGODB_URI=<your-production-mongodb-uri>
EMAIL_FROM=<your-production-email>
GMAIL_USER=<your-gmail>
GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD=<your-app-password>
```

## TypeScript & Type Checking

Environment variables are validated at runtime using Zod (`src/env.ts`).
Invalid or missing critical variables will throw errors during build/startup.
